    "“Closing speed” is what the radar measured as the vehicle approached. Estimated vehicle speed adds your own speed back on, since a car overtaking from behind closes at its speed minus yours.": {
      "localizations": {
        "en-GB": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "“Closing speed” is what the radar measured as the vehicle approached. Estimated vehicle speed adds your own speed back on, since a car overtaking from behind closes at its speed minus yours."
          }
        },
        "en-US": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "“Closing speed” is what the radar measured as the vehicle approached. Estimated vehicle speed adds your own speed back on, since a car overtaking from behind closes at its speed minus yours."
          }
        },
        "de-DE": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Die „Annäherungsgeschwindigkeit“ ist das, was das Radar beim Näherkommen des Fahrzeugs gemessen hat. Die geschätzte Fahrzeuggeschwindigkeit addiert deine eigene Geschwindigkeit, da ein von hinten überholendes Auto mit seiner Geschwindigkeit minus deiner aufschließt."
          }
        },
        "fr-FR": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "La « vitesse d'approche » est ce que le radar a mesuré à l'approche du véhicule. La vitesse estimée du véhicule y ajoute votre propre vitesse, car une voiture qui double par l'arrière approche à sa vitesse moins la vôtre."
          }
        },
        "it-IT": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "La « velocità di avvicinamento » è ciò che il radar ha misurato all'avvicinarsi del veicolo. La velocità stimata del veicolo aggiunge la tua velocità, poiché un'auto che sorpassa da dietro si avvicina alla sua velocità meno la tua."
          }
        },
        "es-ES": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "La « velocidad de aproximación » es lo que midió el radar al acercarse el vehículo. La velocidad estimada del vehículo le suma tu propia velocidad, ya que un coche que adelanta por detrás se acerca a su velocidad menos la tuya."
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "version": "1.0"
}